{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842695857,"sessionID":"ses_2878747b9ffeIS08VEA5449r4J","part":{"id":"prt_d78791551001Du7IMDedvrtVAv","messageID":"msg_d787900130015BbMMtJulQQKo5","sessionID":"ses_2878747b9ffeIS08VEA5449r4J","type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"toolu_70619ba5af424bc6967be196","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"path":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z","pattern":"**/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/*.go"},"output":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation_test.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_test.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/defaults_test.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/defaults.go","metadata":{"count":10,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z","time":{"start":1775842695841,"end":1775842695856}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842695863,"sessionID":"ses_2878747b9ffeIS08VEA5449r4J","part":{"id":"prt_d787909fe00163kTSz4I1XiH0q","messageID":"msg_d787900130015BbMMtJulQQKo5","sessionID":"ses_2878747b9ffeIS08VEA5449r4J","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_68e9f2f2f535443aa867db71","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003: CRD Shared Types & Constants\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal defines shared types and constants for the `pkg/apis` module to be used across CRDs in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n6: \n7: 1. **Centralize common type definitions** - Avoid duplication of types like `ResourceQuota`, `NetworkPolicy`, and lifecycle hooks across multiple CRDs\n8: 2. **Establish naming conventions** - Consistent naming for phases, conditions, and resource types\n9: 3. **Provide reusable validation utilities** - Shared validation functions for common fields\n10: 4. **Enable code generation consistency** - Ensure generated client-go code follows consistent patterns\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n15: **Language:** Go  \n16: **Size:** S\n17: \n18: This AR covers:\n19: \n20: - **In scope:**\n21:   - Common type definitions in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n22:   - Constant definitions for phases and condition types\n23:   - Shared validation utilities\n24:   - Documentation of patterns for future CRDs\n25: \n26: - **Out of scope:**\n27:   - Changes to existing CRD structures (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n28:   - Client-go code generation changes\n29:   - Controller logic modifications\n30: \n31: ## Current State Analysis\n32: \n33: ### Existing Shared Types\n34: \n35: The codebase already has several types that could be considered \"shared\":\n36: \n37: 1. **`ResourceQuota`** (`types.go:80-90`) - CPU, Memory, Storage limits\n38: 2. **`NetworkPolicy`** / `NetworkRule` (`types.go:102-110`) - Network access rules\n39: 3. **`LifecycleHook`** (`types.go:115-123`) - PreStart/PostStop callbacks\n40: 4. **`ContainerSpec`** (`types.go:125-143`) - Container configuration\n41: 5. **`CodeInterpreterSpec`** (`types.go:79-90`) - Embedded interpreter config\n42: \n43: ### Existing Constants\n44: \n45: 1. **AgentRuntimePhase** constants (`types.go:26-36`):\n46:    - `AgentRuntimePhasePending`\n47:    - `AgentRuntimePhaseRunning`\n48:    - `AgentRuntimePhaseFailed`\n49:    - `AgentRuntimePhaseTerminating`\n50: \n51: 2. **AgentRuntimeConditionType** constants (`types.go:38-48`):\n52:    - `AgentRuntimeConditionReady`\n53:    - `AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated`\n54:    - `AgentRuntimeConditionCodeInterpreterReady`\n55: \n56: 3. **AgentRuntimeCondition** struct (`types.go:50-64`) - Reusable condition pattern\n57: \n58: ### Issues Identified\n59: \n60: 1. **Naming inconsistency**: Types are prefixed with `AgentRuntime` but could be more generic\n61: 2. **No shared validation**: Validation logic in `validation.go:171` for `CodeInterpreter` is specific to that type\n62: 3. **No documentation**: No clear guidelines on which types should be shared vs. CRD-specific\n63: 4. **Tight coupling**: `CodeInterpreterSpec` is embedded in `AgentRuntimeSpec` but may need to be standalone\n64: \n65: ## Proposed Changes\n66: \n67: ### 1. Type Categorization\n68: \n69: Introduce clear categorization for types:\n70: \n71: ```\n72: pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n73: ├── types_common.go      # Shared types (ResourceQuota, NetworkPolicy, etc.)\n74: ├── types_agentruntime.go  # AgentRuntime-specific types\n75: └── types_codeinterpreter.go # CodeInterpreter-specific types (if needed)\n76: ```\n77: \n78: **Rationale:** Improves discoverability and makes it clear which types are intended for reuse.\n79: \n80: ### 2. Standardize Type Naming\n81: \n82: Current naming is already consistent with Kubernetes conventions:\n83: - All types use PascalCase\n84: - Related types share prefixes (e.g., `AgentRuntimePhase`, `AgentRuntimeCondition`)\n85: - Embedded structs use descriptive names (`CodeInterpreterSpec`, not just `CodeInterpreter`)\n86: \n87: **No changes needed** - current naming follows Kubernetes API conventions.\n88: \n89: ### 3. Extract Shared Validation\n90: \n91: Create reusable validation functions in `validation.go`:\n92: \n93: ```go\n94: // ValidateResourceQuota validates resource quota fields\n95: func ValidateResourceQuota(quota *ResourceQuota, fldPath *field.Path) field.ErrorList\n96: \n97: // ValidateNetworkPolicy validates network policy configuration\n98: func ValidateNetworkPolicy(policy *NetworkPolicy, fldPath *field.Path) field.ErrorList\n99: \n100: // ValidateContainerSpec validates container specification\n101: func ValidateContainerSpec(spec *ContainerSpec, fldPath *field.Path) field.ErrorList\n102: ```\n103: \n104: **Impact:** Reduces code duplication when adding new CRDs that use these types.\n105: \n106: ### 4. Document Type Usage Patterns\n107: \n108: Add package-level documentation in `doc.go`:\n109: \n110: ```go\n111: // Package v1alpha1 defines the AgentCube runtime API types.\n112: //\n113: // Shared Types:\n114: // Types without AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter prefix are intended for reuse:\n115: // - ResourceQuota: Resource limits and requests\n116: // - NetworkPolicy/NetworkRule: Network access control\n117: // - LifecycleHook: Lifecycle callbacks\n118: // - ContainerSpec: Container configuration\n119: //\n120: // CRD-Specific Types:\n121: // Types prefixed with AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter are specific\n122: // to those CRDs and should not be assumed reusable.\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ### 5. Consider Future CRD Compatibility\n126: \n127: For types that may be used by multiple CRDs:\n128: \n129: **Option A: Keep in v1alpha1 package**\n130: - Simple, no import cycles\n131: - All types in one place\n132: - Risk: Package becomes too large\n133: \n134: **Option B: Extract to `pkg/apis/common`**\n135: - Clearer separation\n136: - Can be imported by multiple API groups\n137: - Risk: Import cycles with scheme registration\n138: \n139: **Recommendation:** Use Option A for now (keep all in `v1alpha1`). Revisit Option B when adding a second API group (e.g., `session.agentcube.volcano.sh`).\n140: \n141: ## Impact Analysis\n142: \n143: ### Files to Modify\n144: \n145: | File | Changes | Impact |\n146: |------|---------|--------|\n147: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Add type usage documentation | Low - documentation only |\n148: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go` | Extract shared validation functions | Medium - affects validation tests |\n149: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Add comments marking shared types | Low - backward compatible |\n150: \n151: ### Backward Compatibility\n152: \n153: All changes are **backward compatible**:\n154: - No existing type signatures change\n155: - Existing CRDs continue to work\n156: - Generated client-go code is unaffected\n157: \n158: ### Testing Impact\n159: \n160: - Existing unit tests continue to pass\n161: - May add tests for shared validation functions\n162: - No integration test changes needed\n163: \n164: ## Alternatives Considered\n165: \n166: ### Alternative 1: Separate Common Package\n167: \n168: Create `pkg/apis/common/types.go` for shared types.\n169: \n170: **Pros:**\n171: - Clear separation of concerns\n172: - Can be imported by multiple API groups\n173: \n174: **Cons:**\n175: - Import cycles with scheme registration\n176: - Over-engineering for single API group\n177: - More complex code generation setup\n178: \n179: **Decision:** Defer until we have multiple API groups.\n180: \n181: ### Alternative 2: Use Kubernetes Core Types\n182: \n183: Replace `ResourceQuota` with `corev1.ResourceRequirements`.\n184: \n185: **Pros:**\n186: - Standard Kubernetes types\n187: - Better integration with ecosystem tools\n188: \n189: **Cons:**\n190: - `corev1.ResourceRequirements` is more complex than needed\n191: - Loses semantic clarity (our `ResourceQuota` has specific meaning)\n192: - Breaking change for existing CRDs\n193: \n194: **Decision:** Keep custom `ResourceQuota` but document mapping to core types.\n195: \n196: ### Alternative 3: Generate Types from Schema\n197: \n198: Use kube-builder markers to generate types from a schema definition.\n199: \n200: **Pros:**\n201: - Single source of truth\n202: - Automatic validation generation\n203: \n204: **Cons:**\n205: - Significant refactoring effort\n206: - Loss of Go type safety during development\n207: - Complex toolchain setup\n208: \n209: **Decision:** Not justified for current project size.\n210: \n211: ## Implementation Checklist\n212: \n213: - [ ] Add package-level documentation in `doc.go`\n214: - [ ] Add comments to shared types in `types.go`\n215: - [ ] Extract shared validation functions in `validation.go`\n216: - [ ] Update validation tests for extracted functions\n217: - [ ] Document patterns in `deployment/client-go.md`\n218: \n219: ## Future Considerations\n220: \n221: 1. **Multiple API Groups**: When adding `session.agentcube.volcano.sh`, reconsider shared type location\n222: 2. **Webhook Validation**: Move validation to admission webhooks for better error messages\n223: 3. **Defaulting Webhooks**: Consider separate defaulting functions for shared types\n224: 4. **Conversion Webhooks**: Plan for v1alpha1 → v1beta1 migration path\n225: \n226: ## References\n227: \n228: - [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://github.com/kubernetes/community/blob/master/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n229: - [Kube-builder Book](https://book.kubebuilder.io/)\n230: - Deployment spec: `deployment/spec.md`\n231: - Client-go documentation: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 231 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003: CRD Shared Types & Constants\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal defines shared types and constants for the `pkg/apis` module to be used across CRDs in the AgentCube project. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Centralize common type definitions** - Avoid duplication of types like `ResourceQuota`, `NetworkPolicy`, and lifecycle hooks across multiple CRDs\n2. **Establish naming conventions** - Consistent naming for phases, conditions, and resource types\n3. **Provide reusable validation utilities** - Shared validation functions for common fields\n4. **Enable code generation consistency** - Ensure generated client-go code follows consistent patterns\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775842695833,"end":1775842695860}}}}
