{"type":"text","timestamp":1775842714160,"sessionID":"ses_2878747b9ffeIS08VEA5449r4J","part":{"id":"prt_d78795e890016NcVeZhFMh4KE9","messageID":"msg_d787954c2001431yHXp81mdmwQ","sessionID":"ses_2878747b9ffeIS08VEA5449r4J","type":"text","text":"Now I have enough context to write the proposal.md for AR-005. Based on the existing AR-004 proposal structure and the codebase, I'll create a comprehensive proposal for the Sandbox creation processor.","time":{"start":1775842714159,"end":1775842714159}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842777075,"sessionID":"ses_2878747b9ffeIS08VEA5449r4J","part":{"id":"prt_d787962310015IxyYLdAJEGhnU","messageID":"msg_d787954c2001431yHXp81mdmwQ","sessionID":"ses_2878747b9ffeIS08VEA5449r4J","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_69c577edc8e542a9bf369d6d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-005/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Sandbox creation processor within the WorkloadManager module for the AgentCube platform. The Sandbox processor is responsible for creating and managing sandboxed execution environments where agent runtimes execute their workloads.\n\nThe Sandbox processor provides:\n\n- **Sandbox lifecycle management** — Create, configure, and destroy sandbox environments\n- **Resource isolation** — Enforce resource quotas and network policies per sandbox\n- **Kubernetes-native implementation** — Deploy sandboxes as Kubernetes pods with appropriate security contexts\n- **Status synchronization** — Update AgentRuntime status based on sandbox state\n- **Cleanup orchestration** — Handle graceful termination and resource cleanup\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **Sandbox Processor Interface** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox.go`)\n   - `SandboxProcessor` interface definition\n   - `Create`, `Delete`, `Get`, `Update` methods\n   - Configuration options for sandbox creation\n\n2. **Sandbox Builder** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_builder.go`)\n   - Pod spec construction from AgentRuntime spec\n   - Security context configuration\n   - Resource quota enforcement\n   - Network policy application\n\n3. **Sandbox Configurator** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_configurator.go`)\n   - Isolation boundary setup\n   - Environment variable injection\n   - Volume mount configuration\n   - Health check probes setup\n\n4. **Resource Allocator** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/resource_allocator.go`)\n   - CPU/memory quota enforcement\n   - Storage allocation\n   - Resource tracking and reporting\n\n5. **Sandbox Status Monitor** (`pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_status.go`)\n   - Pod status polling\n   - Condition updates\n   - Phase transition logic\n\n6. **Integration with AgentRuntime Handler** (`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/agent_runtime.go`)\n   - Trigger sandbox creation on AgentRuntime create\n   - Handle sandbox deletion on AgentRuntime delete\n   - Status synchronization on update\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- WebSocket proxying to sandboxes (deferred to router component)\n- CLI command implementations (Python SDK task)\n- Controller/reconciler loop (separate controller component)\n- Multi-namespace sandbox orchestration (future enhancement)\n- Custom sandbox image management (uses images from AgentRuntime spec)\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Type | Reason |\n|------------|------|--------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Required | Generated Kubernetes client for AgentRuntime |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | Required | Core Kubernetes client for Pod operations |\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Required | Pod, Container, ResourceQuota types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/resource` | Required | Resource quantity parsing |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | Required | AgentRuntime types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | Required | MetaV1 types (ObjectMeta, etc.) |\n| `k8s.io/utils/pointer` | Optional | Pointer utilities |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **AgentRuntime Handler**: Primary consumer of Sandbox processor\n2. **CodeInterpreter Handler**: May use sandbox processor for interpreter isolation\n3. **Controller (future)**: Will use processor for reconciliation logic\n4. **Router**: May query sandbox status for routing decisions\n5. **Python SDK**: Indirect consumer via WorkloadManager HTTP API\n\n### Breaking Changes\n\nNone — this is the initial implementation.\n\n### Migration Path\n\nNot applicable for initial implementation. Future migrations may include:\n- Sandbox spec versioning (`SandboxTemplateSpec` v1 → v2)\n- Security context hardening (breaking change requiring pod recreation)\n- Resource quota model changes (may require sandbox recreation)\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use Kubernetes Jobs instead of Pods\n\n**Approach:** Deploy sandboxes as Kubernetes Jobs with restart policy.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Built-in completion tracking\n- Automatic retry on failure\n- Standard Kubernetes primitive\n\n**Cons:**\n- Jobs are designed for batch workloads, not long-running services\n- More complex status management\n- Harder to inject dynamic configuration\n- Overhead of Job controller\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Agent runtimes are long-running services; Pods provide simpler lifecycle management.\n\n### Alternative 2: Use StatefulSets for Sandboxes\n\n**Approach:** Deploy each sandbox as a StatefulSet with replicas=1.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Stable network identity\n- Persistent volume claims\n- Ordered deployment\n\n**Cons:**\n- Over-engineering for single-pod workloads\n- Slower creation/deletion\n- More complex resource tracking\n- Unnecessary for stateless sandboxes\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. StatefulSets add unnecessary complexity; plain Pods with dynamic configuration are sufficient.\n\n### Alternative 3: Use containerd/shim directly\n\n**Approach:** Bypass Kubernetes and create containers directly via containerd API.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Faster container startup\n- Direct control over container runtime\n- No Kubernetes API overhead\n\n**Cons:**\n- Loses Kubernetes-native benefits (scheduling, resource management)\n- Must implement own scheduling logic\n- Harder to integrate with Kubernetes RBAC\n- Additional operational complexity\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. Kubernetes-native approach aligns with AgentCube architecture and leverages existing cluster infrastructure.\n\n### Alternative 4: Use gVisor or Kata Containers for isolation\n\n**Approach:** Deploy sandboxes with runtime-class for enhanced isolation.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Stronger security isolation\n- Kernel-level separation\n- Better multi-tenant security\n\n**Cons:**\n- Requires cluster-wide runtime-class configuration\n- Performance overhead\n- Not all clusters support custom runtimes\n- Added complexity for initial implementation\n\n**Decision:** Defer to future enhancement. Start with standard Kubernetes security contexts; can add runtime-class support via configuration later.\n\n### Alternative 5: Embed sandbox logic in AgentRuntime controller\n\n**Approach:** Keep sandbox creation inside controller reconcile loop.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Tighter integration with AgentRuntime lifecycle\n- Single place for all logic\n- No additional HTTP layer\n\n**Cons:**\n- Couples HTTP API to controller logic\n- Harder to test sandbox creation independently\n- Controller becomes bloated\n- Violates separation of concerns\n\n**Decision:** Rejected. WorkloadManager processor pattern provides cleaner separation and enables independent testing/scaling.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n1. **Define Sandbox Processor Interface** (`processor/sandbox.go`)\n   ```go\n   type SandboxProcessor interface {\n       Create(ctx context.Context, ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (*SandboxResult, error)\n       Delete(ctx context.Context, ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) error\n       Get(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*SandboxStatus, error)\n       Update(ctx context.Context, ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (*SandboxResult, error)\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **Implement Sandbox Builder** (`processor/sandbox_builder.go`)\n   - Convert AgentRuntime spec to Pod spec\n   - Apply security contexts\n   - Configure resource limits\n   - Set up probes\n\n3. **Implement Resource Allocator** (`processor/resource_allocator.go`)\n   - Parse ResourceQuota from AgentRuntime spec\n   - Validate against namespace quotas\n   - Apply limits to pod spec\n\n4. **Implement Sandbox Configurator** (`processor/sandbox_configurator.go`)\n   - Inject environment variables\n   - Configure volumes\n   - Set up network policies\n\n5. **Implement Sandbox Status Monitor** (`processor/sandbox_status.go`)\n   - Poll pod status\n   - Update conditions\n   - Handle phase transitions\n\n6. **Integrate with AgentRuntime Handler** (`handler/agent_runtime.go`)\n   - Call sandbox processor in CreateAgentRuntime\n   - Call sandbox processor in DeleteAgentRuntime\n   - Add status sync endpoint\n\n7. **Write Unit Tests**\n   - Sandbox builder tests with mock AgentRuntime\n   - Resource allocator tests with various quota configs\n   - Status monitor tests with fake pod informer\n\n8. **Write Integration Tests**\n   - End-to-end sandbox creation with test K8s cluster\n   - Resource quota enforcement tests\n   - Network policy application tests\n\n## Sandbox Architecture\n\n### Pod Spec Structure\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Pod\nmetadata:\n  name: <agentruntime-name>-sandbox\n  namespace: <agentruntime-namespace>\n  labels:\n    agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime: <agentruntime-name>\n    agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox: \"true\"\nspec:\n  securityContext:\n    runAsNonRoot: true\n    runAsUser: 1000\n    fsGroup: 1000\n  containers:\n  - name: sandbox\n    image: <from AgentRuntime spec>\n    command: [from spec]\n    args: [from spec]\n    env: [injected from spec + system vars]\n    resources:\n      limits:\n        cpu: <from ResourceQuota>\n        memory: <from ResourceQuota>\n      requests:\n        cpu: <calculated>\n        memory: <calculated>\n    securityContext:\n      allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n      readOnlyRootFilesystem: true\n      capabilities:\n        drop: [\"ALL\"]\n    livenessProbe:\n      httpGet:\n        path: /healthz\n        port: 8080\n      initialDelaySeconds: 5\n      periodSeconds: 10\n    readinessProbe:\n      httpGet:\n        path: /ready\n        port: 8080\n      initialDelaySeconds: 3\n      periodSeconds: 5\n```\n\n### Resource Allocation Strategy\n\n1. **CPU**: Use `ResourceQuota.CPU` as limit, 50% of limit as request\n2. **Memory**: Use `ResourceQuota.Memory` as limit, 70% of limit as request\n3. **Storage**: Mount ephemeral storage with `ResourceQuota.Storage` limit\n\n### Security Hardening\n\n1. **Non-root user**: Always run as UID 1000\n2. **Read-only root filesystem**: Prevent runtime modifications\n3. **Drop capabilities**: Remove all Linux capabilities\n4. **No privilege escalation**: Block setuid/setgid binaries\n5. **Network policies**: Default deny, explicit allow rules from spec\n\n## API Extension\n\n### New Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes/{name}/sandbox` | Trigger sandbox creation |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes/{name}/sandbox` | Get sandbox status |\n| `DELETE` | `/api/v1/agentruntimes/{name}/sandbox` | Delete sandbox |\n| `GET` | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | List all sandboxes (admin) |\n\n### Response Format\n\n**Sandbox Status Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"my-runtime-sandbox\",\n  \"namespace\": \"default\",\n  \"phase\": \"Running\",\n  \"podName\": \"my-runtime-sandbox-abc123\",\n  \"podIP\": \"10.244.1.5\",\n  \"startTime\": \"2026-04-11T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"conditions\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"Ready\",\n      \"status\": \"True\",\n      \"reason\": \"PodReady\",\n      \"message\": \"Sandbox pod is ready\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"resources\": {\n    \"cpuLimit\": \"1\",\n    \"memoryLimit\": \"512Mi\",\n    \"storageLimit\": \"1Gi\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] SandboxProcessor interface defined and documented\n- [ ] Sandbox builder creates valid pod specs from AgentRuntime\n- [ ] Resource quotas are enforced (CPU, memory, storage)\n- [ ] Security contexts applied correctly (non-root, read-only, no caps)\n- [ ] Network policies configured from AgentRuntime spec\n- [ ] Sandbox status syncs to AgentRuntime status\n- [ ] Unit tests cover all processor methods (>80% coverage)\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with test K8s cluster\n- [ ] Sandbox cleanup on AgentRuntime deletion\n- [ ] Error handling for all failure scenarios (quota exceeded, image pull errors, etc.)\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **SandboxBuilder Tests**\n   - Test pod spec generation with minimal AgentRuntime spec\n   - Test pod spec generation with full AgentRuntime spec\n   - Test security context application\n   - Test resource limit application\n\n2. **ResourceAllocator Tests**\n   - Test quota parsing and validation\n   - Test quota enforcement (success and failure cases)\n   - Test default quota application when not specified\n\n3. **SandboxProcessor Tests**\n   - Test Create() with valid AgentRuntime\n   - Test Create() with invalid spec (missing image)\n   - Test Delete() with existing sandbox\n   - Test Delete() with non-existent sandbox\n   - Test Get() status retrieval\n   - Test Update() resource changes\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **Sandbox Creation Flow**\n   - Create AgentRuntime via HTTP API\n   - Verify sandbox pod created in K8s\n   - Verify pod has correct labels/annotations\n   - Verify resource limits applied\n\n2. **Sandbox Deletion Flow**\n   - Delete AgentRuntime via HTTP API\n   - Verify sandbox pod deleted\n   - Verify cleanup completes within timeout\n\n3. **Status Synchronization**\n   - Verify AgentRuntime status updates when sandbox starts\n   - Verify AgentRuntime status updates when sandbox becomes ready\n   - Verify conditions are correctly populated\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|------------|------------|\n| Resource quota conflicts | Medium | Medium | Validate quotas before pod creation; return clear error messages |\n| Pod stuck in Pending | Medium | Medium | Add timeout handling; provide diagnostic info in status |\n| Security context misconfiguration | High | Low | Use hardened defaults; add validation tests |\n| Sandbox cleanup failures | Medium | Low | Implement finalizer-based cleanup; add retry logic |\n| Network policy not applied | High | Medium | Test with network policy conformance tests; add fallback deny-all |\n\n## Future Considerations\n\n1. **Runtime Class Support**: Add `runtimeClassName` field to AgentRuntime spec for gVisor/Kata\n2. **Persistent Volumes**: Support volume claims for stateful sandboxes\n3. **Sandbox Pooling**: Pre-create sandbox pool for faster startup\n4. **Multi-container Sandboxes**: Support sidecar containers (logging, monitoring)\n5. **Custom Scheduling**: Add node selector/affinity/tolerations to AgentRuntime spec\n6. **Sandbox Snapshots**: Support checkpoint/restore for long-running sandboxes\n\n## References\n\n- [Kubernetes Pods](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/pods/)\n- [Kubernetes Security Context](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/configure-pod-container/security-context/)\n- [Kubernetes Resource Management](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/configuration/manage-resources-containers/)\n- [Kubernetes Network Policies](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/services-networking/network-policies/)\n- Related: `changes/AR-001/` (AgentRuntime CRD)\n- Related: `changes/AR-004/` (WorkloadManager HTTP Service)\n- Related: `deployment/client-go.md`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/agent_runtime.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":122,"character":44},"end":{"line":122,"character":55}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/p